v0.22.0

# Changes

## Infrastructure

 - Using k8s-1.18 at kubevirtci ([#551](https://github.com/nmstate/kubernetes-nmstate/pull/551), [@qinqon](https://github.com/qinqon))

## Other (Bug, Cleanup or Flake)

 - Using `Recreate` strategy for webhook deployment ([#566](https://github.com/nmstate/kubernetes-nmstate/pull/566), [@qinqon](https://github.com/qinqon))

## Uncategorized

 - Bumped operator-sdk to 1.18.0 ([#564](https://github.com/nmstate/kubernetes-nmstate/pull/564), [@qinqon](https://github.com/qinqon))

# Installation

First, install kubernetes-nmstate operator:

```
kubectl apply -f https://github.com/nmstate/kubernetes-nmstate/releases/download/v0.22.0/nmstate.io_nmstates_crd.yaml
kubectl apply -f https://github.com/nmstate/kubernetes-nmstate/releases/download/v0.22.0/namespace.yaml
kubectl apply -f https://github.com/nmstate/kubernetes-nmstate/releases/download/v0.22.0/service_account.yaml
kubectl apply -f https://github.com/nmstate/kubernetes-nmstate/releases/download/v0.22.0/role.yaml
kubectl apply -f https://github.com/nmstate/kubernetes-nmstate/releases/download/v0.22.0/role_binding.yaml
kubectl apply -f https://github.com/nmstate/kubernetes-nmstate/releases/download/v0.22.0/operator.yaml
```

Once that's done, create an `NMState` CR, triggering deployment of
kubernetes-nmstate handler:

```
cat <<EOF | kubectl create -f -
apiVersion: nmstate.io/v1beta1
kind: NMState
metadata:
  name: nmstate
EOF
```
